<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Displays</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.25.0/themes/prism.min.css">
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.25.0/prism.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.25.0/components/prism-lua.min.js"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Displays</h1>
    <p>The major way that you will be communicating information back to the user is through the terminal.</p>
    <p>The easiest way to create text in the terminal is the <strong>print()</strong> method, but another good method is <strong>write()</strong></p>
    <p><strong>print(text)</strong> displays text in the terminal on a new line</p>
    <p><strong>write(text)</strong> displays text in the terminal, but it writes where the last cursor position was. You can determine where the text is written by using <strong>setCursorPos(x, y)</strong>.</p>
    <pre><img src="/img/copy.png" id="lua-copy-image" alt="Copy text" onclick="copyText()"><code class="language-lua" id="toCopy">term.clear()

term.setCursorPos(1, 1) -- The first column of line 1
term.write("First line")

term.setCursorPos(20, 2) -- The 20th column of line 2
term.write("Second line")</code></pre>
    <p><strong>clear()</strong> clears the display as well.</p>
    <br>
    <h2>Colors</h2>
    <p>There are only 16 colors on advanced displays. Colors can only be referenced by using "colors.(color)" (for example, colors.green or colors.black)</p>
    <p>You can change the text color, display background color, or text background color by using the following functions:</p>
    <br>
    <h3>setTextColor(color)</h3>
    <p>Sets the text color</p>
    <pre><img src="/img/copy.png" id="lua-copy-image" alt="Copy text" onclick="copyText()"><code class="language-lua" id="toCopy">print("This text is white")
term.setTextColour(colours.green)
print("This text is green")</code></pre>
    <br>
    <h3>setBackgroundColor(color)</h3>
    <p>Sets the background color for the text. If you use <strong>clear()</strong> right after this, it sets the entire display background color to the color.</p>
    <br>

    <%- sidebar %>

    <a href="https://tweaked.cc/module/term.html" target="_blank">Click here to learn more on tweaked.cc</a>
  </div>

<script>
  function copyText() {
      const parentElement = document.getElementById('toCopy');
      let textToCopy = '';

      for (let i = 0; i < parentElement.childNodes.length; i++) {
          const child = parentElement.childNodes[i];

          textToCopy += child.textContent;
      }

      navigator.clipboard.writeText(textToCopy)
          .then(function() {
              const button = document.getElementById('lua-copy-image')
              button.src = '/img/check.png'
              button.style.height = '25px'
          })
          .catch(function(error) {
              console.error('Unable to copy text to clipboard:', error);
          });
  }
</script>
</body>
</html>
